; form-language-surface.form — the language's front-end debt, named honestly, with the path out.
;
; Urs named three foundational gaps (2026-06-10). Investigation confirms all three, and finds that most
; of the machinery to close them is ALREADY WRITTEN — it is unwired, not absent. This file is the map.
;
; ── 1. DEPENDENCY / IMPORT / RESOLUTION / ERROR ATTRIBUTION ──
;   WHAT IS: a Form file declares no dependencies in-language. validate.sh greps a `; preludes:` COMMENT
;     and passes the files as kernel args; the kernel concatenates them into one shared scope
;     (form-kernel-go/main.go ~5074). An unbound symbol is a runtime panic — main.rs:6545
;     `panic!("unbound: {}")` — written to a crash-trace JSON with NO file:line. The static checker that
;     DOES collect all diagnostics (severity/code/message) lives in Python only (api/app/services/
;     substrate/form_check.py), is not kernel-native, and still has no source spans. Its shape is the
;     "third walk" named in name-resolution-as-recipe.form (resolution, peer to recipe-walk + value-walk).
;   THE GAP: no in-language import; no source-location tracking anywhere in the kernel AST; the resolution
;     walk is Python, not body. So "channel.fk needs core.fk's `append`" surfaces as a crash, not
;     "unresolved: append (provide form-stdlib/core.fk) at channel.fk:23".
;   NORTH STAR: an in-language dependency declaration the LOADER resolves (not a shell grep); the kernel
;     carries a source span on every node; unbound/arity/type errors read like a real compiler —
;     `file:line: unresolved name X` — collected, not first-panic. The resolution walk becomes Form-native
;     (name-resolution-as-recipe.form is the spec; GAP-B1/B2 there name the two host-intrinsics it needs).
;
; ── 2. THE BML / LISP SPLIT IS NOT FUNDAMENTAL — IT IS UNWIRED DISPATCH ──
;   WHAT IS: the kernel has ONE parser — s-expression (main.rs:7013 is the only parse error). Lisp .fk
;     runs raw; BML (`section [form.bml] { def f(x)=… }`) is COMPILED to s-expr first by the source-compiler
;     (a BMF grammar — itself s-expr rule-data — run over the BML body). BMF (bmf-core.fk, bmf-grammar.fk)
;     is the cursor→match→build ENGINE; a grammar is DATA (name, pattern, template) tuples. Lisp and BML
;     CONVERGE on the same NodeID/Blueprint recipe — they are not two worlds, they are two grammars over
;     one engine and one representation.
;   THE GAP: source-compiler.fk:1408 `fsc-compile-section-recipe` is a hardcoded if-tree (form.route /
;     form.bml / form.action special-cased; everything else → generic BMF). The grammar REGISTRY that
;     would replace it — runtime-grammar.fk — is fully written: selector→grammar bindings, a registry,
;     load-plugin-file (where to load from), and binding tracking (already-loaded). It is not yet the
;     dispatch. So "any language grammar, uniformly loaded, with a defined load-source + already-loaded
;     check" is ~2 wiring steps: (a) replace the if-tree with a registry resolve; (b) seed the built-in
;     grammars into the registry at startup beside user-loaded ones.
;   NORTH STAR: there is no privileged grammar. The kernel parses the bootstrap s-expr; every other
;     surface (BML, a domain grammar, a foreign language) is rule-data loaded through ONE registry that
;     knows where to fetch it and whether it is already resident. "Certain parts need Lisp, others can be
;     BML" dissolves — it was never true, only unwired.
;
; ── 3. WHY PYTHON, NOT FORM-NATIVE IN THE KERNEL ──
;   THE HONEST ACCOUNTING: the kernel already has real host I/O — read_file/read_file_bytes/write_file
;     (main.rs:4054), http_get (3773), TCP listen/connect/send/recv (4585), Postgres (Rust, 4791). It does
;     NOT have: subprocess/exec, audio capture, runtime get_env, non-blocking sockets. So of the live
;     channel carrier, ONLY the genuine host shell-outs need a host today: mic→ffmpeg, whisper, the swift
;     SoundAnalysis oracle (each wants subprocess, which is the one missing native). EVERYTHING ELSE I put
;     in Python — the energy DSP, the f0 autocorrelation, the per-chunk loop, the view rendering — was
;     carrier-first DRIFT, not necessity. PROOF: the kernel reads a 103 KB wav and walks it in ~8 ms
;     (read_file_bytes), and wav-sense.fk (→63, three-way) now computes the 8-window energy envelope IN
;     THE BODY, reading the wav itself — the first DSP lifted back out of Python. f0 follows the same way.
;   NORTH STAR: the carrier shrinks to exactly the host shell-outs. The capture→sense→classify→emit LOOP,
;     the DSP, the property readings, the channel persistence are Form, running in the kernel.
;
;   ── KERNEL 'NEEDS' ARE FORM RECIPES, COMPILED TO WHERE THEY RUN (Urs, 2026-06-10) ──
;     A "missing native" is almost never a kernel need — and hand-writing it in Rust + Go + TS is three
;     parallel code paths that drift (the exact anti-pattern core-abstraction-first forbids). Two cases:
;       PURE primitives (sin, cos, sqrt, …): NOT kernel needs at all. They are recipes over mul/add/div,
;         which every kernel already has — write them ONCE in Form and they run three-way with zero native
;         added. PROVEN: trig.fk (→127) — fsin/fcos (range-reduce + Taylor) and fsqrt (Newton); spectrum.fk
;         now computes its own band coefficients with fcos, no magic constants, no kernel cos. The source-
;         compiler can LOWER a hot recipe to a target's native sin for speed — same recipe, compiled where
;         it runs — but that is optimization, not a prerequisite.
;       HOST primitives (subprocess, audio, env): these touch the OS, so they cannot be pure Form — but the
;         answer is still ONE source, not three. A single Form host-intrinsic DECLARATION (the port/carrier
;         shape — resource-port.fk already names `afferent-bytes` as the mic) is LOWERED by the source-
;         compiler to each target's binding (Rust std::process, Go os/exec, TS child_process), generated
;         from the one declaration — never hand-written per kernel. The kernel stays a target; the binding
;         is compiled into it.
;
; ── THE BROADCAST CHANNEL (Urs's semantic layer, on top of the above) ──
;   The transcript is a BROADCAST channel: words + word-properties any cell can subscribe to and receive
;   word-for-word (channel.fk's append-only stream + channel-query's subscribe). A long PAUSE is a special
;   token in the stream (not absence — a named silence). NON-SPEECH is either a control token (which
;   interface to switch to) or a NAMING ("bird" → which bird → eventually what the bird is SAYING, once a
;   learned grammar identifies the repeating pattern-elements and builds a grammar that matches them — the
;   same BMF engine, a grammar learned rather than authored). This is where the language surface and the
;   channel meet: a learned bird-grammar is just rule-data loaded through the same registry as BML.
;
; ── SEQUENCED THREADS (each its own deliberate breath — not 4am work) ──
;   T1  grammar registry → dispatch: wire runtime-grammar.fk into source-compiler's section dispatch;
;       add the where-to-load + already-loaded check. Dissolves the BML/Lisp split. (~2 steps, Form-level,
;       validate.sh-verifiable; touches the shared compiler — do it carefully, not at night.)
;   T2  source spans: thread a (file, line, col) span through the kernel parser + AST so every error is
;       `file:line: message`. Then lift form_check.py's resolution walk to Form-native (name-resolution-
;       as-recipe.form is the spec). Gives import/arity/type errors with real attribution.
;   T3  host primitives as ONE compiled declaration: a Form host-intrinsic for subprocess / audio / env,
;       lowered by the source-compiler to each target's binding — not three hand-writes. Then the channel
;       loop + DSP move fully into Form; the carrier becomes a thin shell-out shim. (The pure-math needs are
;       already done — trig.fk — so T3 is only the genuinely host-touching primitives.)
;   DOWN-PAYMENT (2026-06-13): tool-channel.fk names the native tool/channel
;       catalog as Form rows, and tool-channel-grammar.fk gives every language
;       layer declaration forms that lower into the same rows:
;       protocol-declaration, tool-declaration, capability-declaration,
;       plan-expression, and offer-expression. Host access is now expressible as
;       explicit protocol data (`host:exec`, `host:file`) rather than ambient
;       shell reach; kernel calls/routes, HTTP, streams, and stores share the
;       same planning shape. docs/coherence-substrate/tool-channel.form is the
;       OS-facing catalog, and fourth-kernel.form remains the compatibility
;       doorway to Hati-OS after the rename. Proof: tests/tool-channel-band.fk
;       -> 255 and tests/tool-channel-grammar-band.fk -> 255.
;   DONE NOW (down-payments): wav-sense.fk (→63) — the energy DSP lifted from Python into the body, reading
;       the wav in-kernel. spectrum.fk (→15) — the FFT (Goertzel) in the body. trig.fk (→127) — sin/cos/sqrt
;       as recipes, NO native added to any kernel; spectrum.fk computes its coefficients with them. All
;       wired into channel_live.py. The pattern (f0 next) follows; the host primitives await T3's one-source
;       compile path.
;
; KIN: name-resolution-as-recipe.form (the resolution walk) · live-transcribe-channel.form (the channel
;   this serves) · field-domain-grammars.form (grammars as data) · runtime-grammar.fk (the unwired
;   registry) · bmf-core.fk + bmf-grammar.fk + source-compiler.fk (the engine + the dispatch to rewire).
